<<<<<Small Description>>>>> CPU Environment for Structured/Tabular Machine Learning with scikit-learn, XGBoost, and LightGBM <<<<</Small Description>>>>>
========================================================================================
<<<<<Description>>>>> This container provides a CPU-only environment for training and evaluating models on structured/tabular data. It bundles the standard classical machine learning stack alongside preprocessing, data handling, visualization, and experiment tracking tools. No GPU is required, and training is single-process, single-node by design — well suited to algorithms like gradient-boosted trees that parallelize internally across CPU cores. No project code is baked in — mount your own code and data at run time.

Key Features:
- Classical ML libraries (scikit-learn, XGBoost, LightGBM) for structured/tabular data
- Categorical feature encoding with category-encoders
- Essential data science stack (NumPy, Pandas, SciPy, statsmodels)
- Visualization tools (Matplotlib, Seaborn, Plotly)
- Development environment (JupyterLab)
- CPU-only — no GPU or driver dependency required
- Simple single-node Slurm batch integration <<<<</Description>>>>>
